{"TopicId":170117,"ForumId":51,"TopicTitle":"Baby Buran","CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-26T21:12:09Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-26T21:12:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter a rousing discussion of side-slung launch vehicle balancing at the following thread...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2261781189\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/169916-help-with-buran-style-shuttle/\u0026amp;\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:211px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...I built a full-size Energia-Buran stack and started experimenting with Mun missions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, the complexities of balancing thrust (even if it\u0027s a touch easier than an STS-style shuttle) made me think...just how small an Energia-Buran clone could I manage to make?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMeet...the Baby Buran.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot1.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/tmrlnjxht/screenshot1.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt a scant 10.3 tonnes, it\u0027s hard to imagine anything much smaller. But it does what it\u0027s designed to do!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo room for solar panels and no mass budget for an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E, so it\u0027s all-battery-powered, with a probe core to allow it to do unmanned missions just like its much, much bigger brother. By default, the battery packs on the orbiter are locked so that only the one on the core booster is drained during ascent. It boasts a tiny heat shield on the underside, just in the right place to protect the cockpit, which also allows it to have a lightweight radial\u00A0decoupler.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Lemwig\u0022 sounded like a vaguely Russian name, I thought!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/hkw7tdloh/screenshot2.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust like the real Energia-Buran, the core has four engines and each of the Zenit-clone strap-on boosters has 4 locked nozzles and four gimbaling control nozzles. Of course, here they are all the same size, but no one is looking THAT closely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLiftoff!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/lh9jpe1j5/screenshot3.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTwo of the Oscar-Bs on each side booster are drained to allow a liftoff \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0026gt;1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd Lemwig careens off toward the heavens.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot4.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/ahocdrvoh/screenshot4.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe engines are angled to provide roughly consistent thrust as the fuel tanks drain, but it\u0027s still a bit of a fight. There is a planned roll-over about halfway through ascent, both to take the pilot out of the airstream and to help maintain a good heading.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot6.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/80cl6jecx/screenshot6.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGlamour shot!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot7.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/p0vhf6h3l/screenshot7.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere comes the roll-over.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot8.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/ahocdt5z5/screenshot8.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nApproaching booster burnout. By this point, I\u0027ve already used an action group to cut two of the four booster engines to maintain thrust symmetry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot15.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/s8zysj0w1/screenshot15.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBoosters jettison together, just like Energia-Buran. They do not, however, separate and land independently on chutes, landing legs, and retrothrusters. I am not a god.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot16.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/wuw30urk1/screenshot16.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood trajectory at separation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot17.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/udkbtkcsh/screenshot17.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThrottling down to reduce asymmetric torque below what my reaction wheel can handle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot20.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/avpodnxv5/screenshot20.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBooster burnout! Turning my battery pack back on and preparing for booster separation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot23.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/uqbpzt081/screenshot23.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood separation. My two linear thrusters kick on to push me into orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot24.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/wuw30w9kh/screenshot24.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe burn shouldn\u0027t actually be too terribly long.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIgnore the maneuver node; the apoapse is way higher than I\u0027ll actually be going to. Just wanted a good maneuver vector.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot26.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/nzv8qe07l/screenshot26.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIsn\u0027t it cute?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot29.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/ope12rvm9/screenshot29.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd we\u0027ve got a good orbit!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot32.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/k3hwufpip/screenshot32.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGranted, that\u0027s not a LOT of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E for stuff to do in space, but with a good intercept you could rendezvous with a space station. Or it could be sent up unmanned to rescue a stranded Kerbal, thanks to that probe core.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, with no further ado, here\u0027s the deorbit burn!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot34.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/3trqqyme9/screenshot34.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI ended up quickloading because my first attempt didn\u0027t get me anywhere near the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E, and for some reason my landing gear glitched into an odd position. Oh well; can\u0027t be helped!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot36.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/46j4x5k3l/screenshot36.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nComing in hot, but it\u0027s nothing this kool Kerbal can\u0027t handle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot39.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/46j4x5zj5/screenshot39.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHonestly was more worried about that landing gear.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot41.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/gl5wxi6gx/screenshot41.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey, lookee there! We just might make it!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot43.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/ak880fza9/screenshot43.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNosing forward to get a better glide ratio.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot44.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/egljwgf4x/screenshot44.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrying to turn...my inclination was a bit off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot48.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/fivqf0ddt/screenshot48.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBurning off remaining monoprop to extend my range and lighten my load. Besides, who wants that nasty hydrazine still in the tanks with an open-cockpit deadstick landing?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot50.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/o156jczc1/screenshot50.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like a good descent.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot57.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/956nbtldd/screenshot57.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLining up for landing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot59.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/js0gh8lsx/screenshot59.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLast-moment corrections.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot61.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/qv8bwvm3l/screenshot61.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill I make it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy, I do believe I will.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot65.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/6b3hyels1/screenshot65.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere we go! Let\u0027s hope that wonky landing gear holds up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot66.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/46j4xbzkx/screenshot66.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTouchdown!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot67.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/u22vgk3zl/screenshot67.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd, done.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot70.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/3trqr64gh/screenshot70.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe\u0027s happy to be back!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot71.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/qigxqqtk1/screenshot71.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-26T21:16:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is awesome!\u00A0 Any chance you can share the craft file?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-26T21:21:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223278484\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170117\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221517001361\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179753\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Geonovast\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Geonovast said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is awesome!\u00A0 Any chance you can share the craft file?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! And sure, here you go!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://files.fm/u/9pxnwgpb#_\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://files.fm/u/9pxnwgpb#_\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jack5.exe","CreatedById":178702,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-26T21:54:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow about a payload version?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-26T21:59:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223278522\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170117\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221517003647\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022178702\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jack5.exe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Jack5.exe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow about a payload version?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRecoverable or no? If you don\u0027t need it to be recoverable (e.g., Energia-Polyus), just make the booster stack into a subassembly and replace the orbiter with your encapsulated payload.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you need it to be recoverable...well, what payload exactly do you intend to fit in that small of a space?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jack5.exe","CreatedById":178702,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-26T22:01:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223278528\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170117\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221517003988\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRecoverable or no? If you don\u0027t need it to be recoverable (e.g., Energia-Polyus), just make the booster stack into a subassembly and replace the orbiter with your encapsulated payload.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you need it to be recoverable...well, what payload exactly do you intend to fit in that small of a space?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nstarter payload... the second smalled octagonal grey control thgy\u00A0and an antenna on it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-26T22:03:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would consider the Kerbal to be the Payload.\u00A0 Stuff like this would be good for Space Station crew rotation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-26T22:04:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223278532\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170117\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221517004181\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179753\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Geonovast\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Geonovast said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would consider the Kerbal to be the Payload.\u00A0 Stuff like this would be good for Space Station crew rotation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndeed. Of course, I can build a small recoverable \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E to do the same job, but this is still pretty darn small.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223278530\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170117\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221517004069\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022178702\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jack5.exe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, Jack5.exe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nstarter payload... the second smalled octagonal grey control thgy\u00A0and an antenna on it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s what I suppose you might do if you wanted a payload version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot0.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://s14.postimg.org/3q2z7z7up/screenshot0.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe heat shield and command seat are\u00A0removed and the front cone has been attached to the rear node of the orbiter, then rotated and translated up. The whole profile has been elongated slightly to fit the payload. Should handle roughly the same on ascent and re-entry, though without batteries or solar power that starter payload isn\u0027t going to be transmitting for long.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NotAgain","CreatedById":150764,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-31T13:48:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelp. That was impressive.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"roboslacker","CreatedById":175473,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-06T16:51:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s so cute.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}